node.text:
Well.. I’m a woman of my word. 
3 likes = Tree climb. 
I understand there is a lot of stress and uneasiness in regards to current events. My contributions to these events are not always on social media - and that’s ok! Big differences can also be made off screen. We all function in different ways. Continue to be yourself. This is meant to be mindless and something you can enjoy for a few minutes.

Stay tuned for more challenges. Suggestions?

The ending 😂😂

node.text: THE MOST NERVOUS IVE EVER BEEN IN MY LIFE - so I thought I’d share. Enjoy

node.title: 7th event of 7. 2018 NCAA 800m .. Can’t wait for more moments like this

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Georgia Ellenwood on August 09, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
The Olympics are over. I’m sad. Mostly because I have to cook and do my laundry again. 

What should be my first off-season activity? McDonald’s? g&t (Or 3) ? Sleep until noon? Ahh the possibilities ..

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Georgia Ellenwood on August 05, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and playing a sport.

node.text:
Wow. That was one of the toughest things I’ve ever had to endure.. but I didn’t make it to the Olympics just to make it to the Olympics. I woke up this morning feeling like I got hit by a train. I tried to push through the first couple of events but the nausea, fatigue and dizziness kept building. I faced the worst of it in the hours before the 800m. If I breathed too deep, I would vomit. 🤭 dehydration? Heat stroke? Not quite sure

I had to dig deeper than I’ve EVER had to before in a competition. I was going to finish, one way or another. Thank you everyone for the love and support - I am still recovering but I am SO proud of myself for finding my way across the line today. What a way to turn 26.. 

Congrats to Damian - OLYMPIC CHAMP!!! And Pierce for being an absolute beast. We are fighters. Canadian multi events. ❤️🇨🇦

node.text:
Thank you Gifu!!!! Our prep camp has come to an end… we move to the Olympic Village today for final tune ups. I’m so inspired by watching Team Canada and other Olympians make their dreams come true. I fully expect for this Heptathlon to be two gruelling, mentally challenging and sleep deprived days. That’s nothing new. I’m going to go out there and challenge myself - and hopefully have a little fun doing it. Let’s go! 😈
#gifucanada

node.text:
I really freaking did it!!!! I made the decision to stay in Europe after Götzis to give it my all in one more competition. I was completely alone, training for a month and then competed without a coach or any family at Ratingen. I’ve been underestimated because of my size, I’ve fallen short on multiple occasions, and I’ve even questioned myself if I’m worthy to be one of the world’s best. I had such a strong team cheering me on from home and I felt their energy throughout the entire competition. Today I said “why not me?”. 
.
.
Thank you Ratingen for putting on an incredible meet, and to the other athletes for being so welcoming. I will remember this forever ❤️

If there’s no mark on the plasticine, it’s a fair jump! I decided to play with fire and it paid off 😂😂😂.. 

6224pts overall; a PB and 3rd best score ever by Canadian Heptathlete! I still have A LOT more to give. 

All the Canadian’s PBed in Götzis. Soon they might make the combined events our official national sport! Right behind Hockey!  lol.. imagine that
